headline: Grasberg mine accident tightens global copper supply estimates
summary: LONDON (Reuters) -Metals analysts are cutting their estimates of global copper supplies for this year and next after an accident at the giant Grasberg mine dramatically tightened the outlook for the market.  Copper prices hit 15-month highs of $10,485 a metric ton last week after Freeport-McMoRan declared force majeure at its Grasberg mine and cut sales forecast from the Indonesian unit for this year and 2026.  Freeport's Grasberg operation located in Indonesia suspended operations on September 8 after a deadly mud slide.

headline: FCX Upgraded, Leads S&P 500 After Copper Mine Disaster
summary: Freeport-McMoRan was the top S&P 500 performer early Tuesday after an upgrade from BofA analyst Lawson Winder, who spoke with CEO Kathleen Quirk about the recovery effort following a Sept. 8 disaster at the world's second-largest copper mine.  FCX stock built on Monday's bounce-back session, attempting to regain long-term support.  While upgrading FCX stock to buy from neutral, BoA reiterated its 42 price target — 12% above where shares ended Monday's session.
